You can still check your Gig status with this tool on Fiverr Help & Support | Fiverr 19
Click on My gig doesn’t appear in search, then choose each gig one by one. It will show you if your gigs are active or not.

@markadamsdesign Your discussion makes sense. You have such a unique gig. I assume most here have gigs that are more traditional.
My theory is that if your gigs can have a way to stand out somehow from the rest in a good way then you won’t need the analytics, for those who are in a highly competitive group of sellers. That way might simply be having outstanding talent.
If a seller has been plodding along with bad graphics and a gig that doesn’t stand out somehow from the rest and getting impressions and sales they’ve been very lucky. That might be changing now that half the world’s population has suddenly decided to become sellers on fiverr.

Also, the amount of orders you get depends on how saturted the market in which your gigs are.
Logo design for instances has 98,486 gigs on Fiverr today. That is a great deal of competition for work. On the other hand proofreading and writing content has around 13,500 each.
